.\" $Id$
.\" The following macro turns the program name in uppercase letters.
.de uppercase
.  tr aAbBcCdDeEfFgGhHiIjJkKlLmMnNoOpPqQrRsStTuUvVwWxXyYzZ
.  di uppercase
.    nop \\*[\\$1]
.    br
.  di
.  asciify uppercase
.  chop uppercase
.  tr aabbccddeeffgghhiijjkkllmmnnooppqqrrssttuuvvwwxxyyzz
.  ds \\$2 \\*[uppercase]\"
..
.\" Define the program name in its original and uppercase forms.
.ds name gcrystal@STABILITY@
.uppercase name NAME
.de prog
.  B gcrystal@STABILITY@
..
.\" Begin manual page.
.TH "\*[NAME]" "1" "@GCU_API_VER@" "gnome-chemistry-utils @VERSION@" "User commands"

.SH "NAME"
\*[name] \- light model visualizer for crystal structures

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.prog
.B [options]
.BI [ file ]

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
.prog
is a light model visualizer for crystal structures, based on the GNOME Chemistry
Utils, that displays models of all sorts of crystal microscopic structures using
OpenGL.

.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
The following options are accepted:

.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help ", " \-\-help-all
Show application help options. Also refer to
.BR gnome-options "(7) and"
.BR gtk-options (7).

.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version information.

